org.modelio.api.module

Class AbstractJavaModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelio.api.module.AbstractJavaModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IModule

    public abstract class AbstractJavaModule
extends Object
implements IModule
    Default implementation of the IModule interface.

    All Modelio java modules should inherit from this class.

      • init

        public void init()
        Description copied from interface: IModule
        Method automatically called just after the creation of the module.

        The module is automatically instantiated at the beginning of the mda lifecycle and the constructor implementation is not accessible to the module developer.

        The init method allows the developer to execute the desired initialization code at this step. For example, this is the perfect place to register any IViewpoint this module provides.

        This method should never be called by the developer because it is already invoked by the tool.

        Specified by:
        init in interface IModule

      • uninit

        public void uninit()
        Description copied from interface: IModule
        Method automatically called just before the disposal of the module.

        The uninit method allows the developer to execute the desired un-initialization code at this step. For example, if IViewpoints have been registered in the IModule.init() method, this method is the perfect place to remove them.

        This method should never be called by the developer because it is already invoked by the tool.

        Specified by:
        uninit in interface IModule
